#: includes/admin/documentation.php:142
msgid "Email Template Customization"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/documentation.php:143
msgid "All plugin emails use a shared HTML wrapper so registration links, assignment confirmations, cancellations, and announcements have a consistent look."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/documentation.php:144
msgid "Integrators can customize or fully replace this wrapper in theme code or a small companion plugin using WordPress filters."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/documentation.php:146
msgid "Adjust template variables such as heading, preheader, site name, or footer text before the final HTML is generated."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/documentation.php:147
msgid "Modify only the inner email body HTML while keeping the default wrapper."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/documentation.php:148
msgid "Replace the complete final HTML output if you need a fully custom branded layout."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/documentation.php:150
msgid "Example: add this in your theme’s functions.php or a small custom plugin to change the footer text of all EventAdmin emails."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/documentation.php:155
msgid "Use a custom plugin instead of editing EventAdmin directly if you want your changes to survive plugin updates."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/documentation.php:157
msgid "Automatic Cleanup of Unverified Accounts"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/documentation.php:158
msgid "A daily background job automatically deletes volunteer accounts that were registered via the public form but whose magic login link expired without ever being clicked. Accounts are only deleted if they have no shift assignments and are not marked as manually added."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/documentation.php:159
msgid "A log of automatically deleted accounts (up to the last 100) is shown at the bottom of the Volunteers page."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/documentation.php:161
msgid "Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/documentation.php:163
msgid "Do volunteers need an account?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/documentation.php:164
msgid "Yes, they must be logged in to view and join shifts."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/documentation.php:166
msgid "How can I assign volunteers manually?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/documentation.php:167
msgid "In the admin dashboard under “Volunteer Overview” for each shift via form."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/documentation.php:169
msgid "What happens when shifts are full?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/documentation.php:170
msgid "By default, full shifts are hidden on the volunteer page. You can optionally show them in a separate read-only section by enabling \"Show full shifts to volunteers\" under Settings."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/documentation.php:172
msgid "What is the minimum volunteers field for?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/documentation.php:173
msgid "You can set a minimum number of volunteers per shift. The admin dashboard will highlight shifts that have not reached the minimum with an understaffing warning. This is informational only – no signup rules are enforced based on the minimum."
msgstr ""

